description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trainee Care Support Worker - &lt;strong&gt;Coventry &amp; Warwickshire Partnership NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Locations covered&lt;strong&gt;: Caludon Centre, Clifford Bridge Road&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking to start a rewarding career in Mental Health with the NHS?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We can offer dedicated candidates highly sought after NHS experience through a valuable training program, in partnership with a prestigious NHS Mental Health Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals are currently recruiting Trainee Care Support Workers for Coventry &amp; Warwickshire Partnership NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for candidates who are working in a ‘care/health background’ (see listed criteria below).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to consider candidates with at least &lt;strong&gt;3 months&lt;/strong&gt; experience within the last 2 years in the following care backgrounds:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Criteria&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Domiciliary Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Nursing home / complex care at patients home&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Ambulance Technician experience;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Candidates trained by military and working as a medic in military / military hospital setting; and experience of nursing home / complex care (health) at patients own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Attendance of Assessment Day – &lt;strong&gt;3rd December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Attendance of FREE classroom training –&lt;strong&gt;11th to15th &lt;strong&gt;January 2021 &lt;/strong&gt;(Monday to Friday)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Attendance of FREE Trust Training (MAPA) – week commencing &lt;strong&gt;18th&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;January 2021 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Monday to Friday)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Placements starting from &lt;strong&gt;February 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 37.5 hours supervised placements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 30 hours per week for 3 months (earlies, lates and nights pro rata)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supernumerary (Induction Week) Rates of Pay&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days £8.21&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nights / Saturday £11.74&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sunday / Bank Holiday £15.27&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hourly Rates of Pay during the programme:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days £8.37&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nights / Saturday £12.14&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sunday / Bank Holiday £15.90&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hourly Rates of Pay on completion of the programme:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days £9.03&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nights / Saturday £12.82&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sunday / Bank Holiday £16.61&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patient safety is our number one priority and continuity of patient care is essential, so we would only like to hear from applicants who are able to meet the availability required to fulfil the placement criteria, have a keen interest in the care profession and meet the basic requirements for Maths and English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for this commitment, we can offer you a rewarding fresh start in a new career or further experience on other wards and specialties, as well as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Weekly pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Paid annual leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Statutory maternity pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Training and development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Upon successful completion of the programme, as an NHS Professional - Flexible Worker you will have the added benefit and opportunity to continue to work as a Care Support Worker and undertake flexible shifts that suit you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please only apply if you are able to attend the Classroom Training Dates above.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When Applying please make sure you complete the following sections correctly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;References – Please provide the details of a work referee for every job you have had in the past 3 years. NHS Professionals do not accept personal email addresses, mobile numbers or email accounts i.e. Hotmail/yahoo/Gmail of referees. Please also note personal references such as friends, relatives or colleagues are not acceptable. Failure to provide the correct reference information can cause significant delays to your start date and may result in your application being unsuccessful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment history – we require 3 years continuous employment to be able to process your application. To continue to the next section please make sure there are no gaps in the dates for all of your employment history. Enter any period of unemployment or studies as if they were jobs. Your current employment does not have an end date.&lt;/p&gt;
